&quot;Baysha sherum!&quot; He yelled, &quot;Baysha sherum!&quot; he repeated. &quot;Baysha sherum!&quot; he demanded. Each time sending torrents of explosions about him causing the subterranean structures to follow on the commoners and guards alike. The guards continued to attack the shadows, and ever time it weakned him. &quot;You will not stop my rage!&quot; The bringer of darkness cried out his voice resonating like a crisp morning chill.<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;Woius diwa iestafen liustam!&quot; He yelled at the closest guard, his shadow self lurched like his mortal self once did. The guard fell lifeless, and he felt full. &quot;Woius diwa iestafen liustam!&quot; He repeated this seemed to restore his strength as the guards fell about him. He could feel their spirits join his darkness. &quot;Woius diwa iestafen liustam!&quot; He cried out again causing a guard to stop in mid run his blade flew through the air which The Bringer of darkness side stepped. It skewed a drow that was fleeing.<br>
<br>
It was not woman and children who fled, it was children and men. The females had all the nerves in drow colonies. They would not be so easily defeated and the fleeing drow did not get far, as the darkness surrounded them, cut them, entered them and molested them with it's short blade. Tearing, cutting, ripping at any flesh that was in his view. The silver streets became tarnished by the blood of his brethren.<br>
<br>
&quot;Estam ama kan!&quot; Cried a voice from far away, and then lightning bolts seared from the hands of a drow mage burning at his shadow self. <br>
<br>
&quot;Fleis far!&quot; He responded, &quot;Fleis far!&quot; he demanded and &quot;Fleis far!&quot; he raged. Fire enveloped any flammable structure and confused any near by mage. Children where scorched alive, and The Bringer kept on cutting at his brothers and sisters with his blade.<br>
<br>
They too would find silence in his darkness. His internal peace would be there's once they over came the anguish of his slaying them. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
As the battle raged all black drow dead lay about him, their life force ripped from their ash skin. Red blood spilled from those whom died from his blade over the silver streets. The thin cutters which were used to redirect water that filtered down in rain now filtered the blood of his brothers.<br>
<br>
Rats and denizens from below scurried over the corpses drawn to the scene by the smell of fresh death. He continued to get charged by warrior males, the females began sending volleys of lightning at him from behind their battle armor. <br>
<br>
They lightning bolts blinded him as they reflected off the females silver armor and seared through his dark ghostly body.  They passed effortlessly through him, but their magical properties where relentless causing him to groan inside form the anguish of the constant volley.<br>
<br>
He was becoming weak, he would not perish by the females. They gave birth to him, they made him fight in the pits, they made him the outcast. His rage brought new life and new vigor.<br>
<br>
&quot;Estam ama kan!&quot; Cried the females a constant volley of their thunderous powers. The light continued to flash through him. He was numb from the pain, his anger was to strong.<br>
<br>
&quot;Woius diwa iestafen liustam!&quot; Was his only rseponce to their screams. As the first woman fell he watched the glory of birth as they joined him in his darkest womb. They would be his eternal children locked inside his ghastly cloud of darkness.<br>
<br>
He charged the steps the bolts of lightning flying about him, the men no longer pursued him because the volley of lightning was to thick. As he charged the steps screaming &quot;Woius diwa iestafen liustam!&quot; The females before him fell. Instead of stopping to slay them with his sword he charged forward past them, the large trail of darkness that flew like a war banner behind him enveloped them blinding them in his darkness. <br>
<br>
He charged to the throne where the queen was armed with her sword throwing volleys of lightning with her free hand. He did not scream any magical incantations he embraced her like a mother does his child. Her screams where horror as she felt his hands overcome her, she swung wildly with her sword. He was not phased he hugged her with his horrific body tightly his shadowed fog solidifying about her.<br>
<br>
The hug of his blackness turned to a constricting grip the queen fainted in his dark arms she was not dead but asleep at his feet. Before this day they had made him the outcast, now he had made himself one. The outcast king, bringer of darkness he slowly turned about the bolts of lightning had stopped his darkness collected itself about his being.<br>
<br>
The drow breathed heavily, the wounded fought off the rats and carrion crawlers whom tried to eat them alive. The females on the silver steps had their back to him, staring towards the other part of town. There entered a loud thunder as if a large creature was approaching.<br>
<br>
Then from the darkness he had created entered a large crystaline dragon who's skin shimmered but it's transparency gave way to it's creation. Gears where inside of it and upon it's back was Jarasmine. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
The dragon roared it's gears releasing steam. Its large feet crushed the dead beneath them. Jarasmine's calm demeanor was present in him again, only moments of insanity flicked in and out of his blue pupils. Jarasmine stepped off his steed sliding to the ground. <br>
<br>
&quot;Unification under one Teir'Dal&quot; Bellowed Jarasmine. &quot;The Bringer of Darkness has forced the drow to listen.&quot; Jarasmine's plan was coming into play. He wanted unification but he could not let the Bringer live in his current state. Jarasmine feared the bringer but he had made preparations and calculated many things.<br>
<br>
Jarasmine looked upward at the large throne shrouded in the presence of the Bringer of darkness. The staircase was littered with the dead princess drow, and the queen at his feet. Some drow remained alive dispersed about the colony there forces still large but there was nothing they could to against the bringer. He was the darkness they had cultivated for years with their dark ways. <br>
<br>
Jarasmine looked to the dragon and nodded. The Large golem's mouth opened and aimed upward at the stalagtite covered ceiling. A large projectile issued forth from the creatures mouth exploding on contact with the ceiling which broke and gave way. Moon light pierced through the crack of the opening shining down on the throne.<br>
<br>
The bringer of darkness revolted and churned inside himself. Jarasmine had sentenced the bringer to slavery once again inside a mortal body. The bringers body solidified and formed once again to that of a drow. His skin began to radiate and the darkness retreat slowly into his eyes.<br>
<br>
Drundam bent over vomiting, the pain of transformation was tremendous. He screamed through heaves his eyes shed tears that did nothing to wash away his sins and shame. He slowly rose above them, he did not whipe his lips. The taste of death was on them and he held down the little acid that was left in his stomach. The tears in his right eye stopped, but his left eye was relentless and coalesced on his chin then fell down across his chest. His tears slowly flowed over the rest of his naked body where they touched that of the fallen queen who slept.<br>
<br>
He was proud for the first time. He had conquered his own people he held with his right arm his sword high. The living drow beneath him screamed in rage and support. Any other race save demons would have been furious.<br>
<br>
This day Drundam had experienced the death of his people, and the glory of his race. He was a moon drow, King of the Moon and would unify the Tears of the drow. <br>
